  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: cd20df6c9479f3d449851f4ca53de79e, type: 3}
  m_Name: BeastsBook
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  bookTitle: Beasts
  spreads:
  - layout: {fileID: 6211519498159910813, guid: 274d6efd15c355843aab952415fd5afe, type: 3}
    textA: 'The local animals have been changing over the last few years. Mainly
      the deer, but they are not deer anymore.


      Maybe they kept the form to
      hunt prey easier?


      I will try to keep a log of these beasts in this
      book. '
    textB: 
    textC: 
    textD: 
    imageA: {fileID: 865804816067458902, guid: c613b4c540c83ac4ba00ad0bee065134, type: 3}
    imageB: {fileID: 0}
    imageC: {fileID: 0}
    imageD: {fileID: 0}
  - layout: {fileID: 470820575514630869, guid: a5e688b43a5f7f44598b6b05ea243423, type: 3}
    textA: Skinwalker Stag
    textB: Some wear the skin poorly. The legs bend wrong. The head lags behind the
      body.
    textC: Do not look away. It cannot hold the shape forever. It relies on darkness
      to hide. I took a photo of it to study it, but that seemed to weaken it.
    textD: 
    imageA: {fileID: 8191607871805606840, guid: 7909af0775c51c643afc2a28723c90f6, type: 3}
    imageB: {fileID: -8579180617657454444, guid: ae45ff052776b1840be37ac3d2a07621, type: 3}
    imageC: {fileID: 0}
    imageD: {fileID: 0}
  - layout: {fileID: 470820575514630869, guid: 1a4ce467c9bbd91459e6f1d16a4f9a9e, type: 3}
    textA: 
    textB: Is it possible the simple act of observing it weakens it?
    textC: This would explain why it avoids trail cameras...
    textD: '

'
    imageA: {fileID: 8274388944355335981, guid: 7323464a9002fa14ebf2f361d2a47928, type: 3}
    imageB: {fileID: 0}
    imageC: {fileID: 0}
    imageD: {fileID: 0}
  - layout: {fileID: 4469434606004700145, guid: b1f56c105ade1124b882fddd07899040, type: 3}
    textA: Many-Eyed Stag
    textB: Break the sight!
    textC: And the body follows.
    textD: 'There are others that do not hide. They watch....Not just from the body.


      The
      eyes grow where they are needed. On walls. In the dark. Behind you....


      If
      it cannot see you, it cannot hunt you!

'
    imageA: {fileID: -5926201026390796380, guid: 7bda3dac18202074c9e330f707aabd49, type: 3}
    imageB: {fileID: 0}
    imageC: {fileID: 0}
    imageD: {fileID: 0}
  - layout: {fileID: 3969447794958561858, guid: 7c421c19313b57743bb1e86d950a6803, type: 3}
    textA: Sound Stag
    textB: 'Although it has eyes, it hunts using sound. I don''t think it can see
      at all.


      It''s hearing is incredible though.


      It heard my headphones
      playing music quietly over a kilometer away!


'
    textC: 
    textD: '

'
    imageA: {fileID: 865804816067458902, guid: d7bf469b62ce5af4985a453e6e243d87, type: 3}
    imageB: {fileID: 3254737427981163177, guid: 09f0072bacf1099408db4e4f43708378, type: 3}
    imageC: {fileID: 1507147114455510500, guid: 0450db69b07592147a312c658377ad6f, type: 3}
    imageD: {fileID: 0}
  - layout: {fileID: 6211519498159910813, guid: 274d6efd15c355843aab952415fd5afe, type: 3}
    textA: 'If you seen this in the forest you must REMAIN QUIET!


      Turn off
      any music, don''t breath too loudly, and if your on a call, MUTE THE CALL!'
    textB: 'Here is a larger sketch to identify it better.

'
    textC: 
    textD: '

'
